cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SY

This paper is about evolutionary deep intelligence, which involves the synthesis of deep neural networks through evolutionary algorithms. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also discusses the impact of external factors on the network synthesis process, which could fall under sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the study uses a subset of the MNIST dataset, which is commonly used in computer vision research, suggesting a potential fit for cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper mentions the potential application of the synthesized networks in control systems, which could fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control).
